# No Mock Data Implementation

This project strictly prohibits the use of mock data, dummy data, or hardcoded test data in any form. All data must come from real backend sources.

## Forbidden Practices

- ❌ Creating mock objects or fake API responses
- ❌ Hardcoded test data in components
- ❌ Fake user objects, courses, or any domain data
- ❌ Mock services or repositories
- ❌ Static JSON files with sample data

## Required Practices

- ✅ All data must come from actual backend APIs
- ✅ Use real database connections and queries
- ✅ Implement proper error handling for API failures
- ✅ Use loading states while fetching real data

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Mock data
const mockCourses = [
  { id: 1, title: "React Basics", instructor: "John Doe" },
  { id: 2, title: "Advanced TypeScript", instructor: "Jane Smith" }
];

// ✅ GOOD - Real data from API
const { data: courses, isLoading } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['courses'],
  queryFn: () => apiClient.get('/courses')
});
```